RABIES, EQUINE - FINLAND:OIE
***************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>;
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>;

Date: 24 June 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Office International des Epizooties(OIE), Disease Information [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_14.HTM#Sec0>;

Rabies in Finland in an imported horse
--------------------
Emergency report
Information received on 13 and 16 Jun 2003 from Dr Riitta Heinonen, Deputy
Director General, Veterinary and Food
Department, Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry, Helsinki:
Report date: 16 Jun 2003.
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 11 Jun 2003.
Outbreaks:
Location: in western Finland
No. of outbreaks: 1
Description of affected population: an imported horse.
Total number of animals in the outbreak:
species -- equine
susceptible -- 1
cases -- 1
deaths -- 0
destroyed -- 1
slaughtered -- 0
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: National Veterinary and Food
Research Institute.
B. Diagnostic tests used: fluorescent antibody test. On 16 Jun 2003
confirmatory results were obtained by cell culture.
Source of agent / origin of infection: horse imported on 8 May 2003 from a
neighbouring country.
Note by the OIE Animal Health Information Department: The latest indigenous
case of rabies reported to the OIE by Finland occurred in February 1989 (in
wildlife). In Finland, rabies occurrence has never been recorded in horses.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The posting, Rabies (EBLV 2), human - UK (Scotland): conf (04)
20021213.6054 referenced below, indicated a rabies-like disease had
occurred in Finland in1985. This was an EBL 2 European Bat Lyssavirus
infection that occurred in a human who handled bats. - Mod. PC]
